definitions.definition: A freshwater fish of the genus Barbus or other closely related genera.
Whisker-like sensory organs, located around the mouth of certain fish, including catfish , carp , goatfish , sturgeon , and some types of shark.
A barb or pap under the tongues of horses and cattle .
